						               													<description>Scoop is a series of fast-paced word games where players compete to make three-letter words.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game has 35 target cards, 2.25&amp;quot; x 2.25&amp;quot;, with single letters, and 150 cards, 1.15&amp;quot; x 1.15&amp;quot;, with bigrams (two letters); all cards have point values. There are rules for 4 different games. In all but one of them the bigrams are all face up on the table for all to scoop from.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1. Be Quick: Reveal a target card, and everyone has 15 seconds to gather as many bigrams as they can that make a word with that card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2. Elimination: Reveal a target card, and each player chooses one of their 10 bigrams to make a word with it. The one with the highest-scoring word gets the points of all the cards revealed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3. Winner Takes All: Each player chooses one of their 3 letter cards and takes a bigram to go with it. The one with the highest-scoring word gets the points of all revealed cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4. Scoop Five: Each player takes five bigrams, one for each of their five letter cards.  Each player scores the points for each of their words made.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
